The paper deals with uncertainty principles and sparse signal processing, which are topics that are commonly studied in the information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SP), numerical analysis (cs.NA), machine learning (cs.LG), and statistics (cs.SI) communities. The use of numerical sparsity as a continuous proxy for the 0-norm suggests a focus on numerical methods, which is more closely related to cs.NA than to cs.LG or cs.SI. However, the paper also discusses the consequences of the new uncertainty principles in various sparse signal processing applications, which suggests a closer connection to cs.SP and cs.LG. Overall, cs.IT, cs.SP, cs.NA, cs.SI, and cs.LG are all likely sub-categories for this paper.
